  "prompt": "Do you think Indian education system is good?",
  "response": "The Indian education system has both strengths and challenges:\n\nStrengths:\n1. Strong emphasis on science and mathematics\n2. High-quality technical and engineering education\n3. Producing skilled professionals globally\n4. Affordable education compared to many countries\n5. Growing digital learning opportunities\n\nChallenges:\n1. Overcrowded classrooms\n2. Rote learning approach\n3. Limited practical and skill-based learning\n4. High competition and exam pressure\n5. Uneven quality between urban and rural schools\n6. Insufficient focus on creativity and critical thinking\n7. Limited industry-academia collaboration\n\nWhile the system has notable achievements, significant reforms are needed to improve overall quality and prepare students for future challenges. Recent initiatives like National Education Policy 2020 aim to address some of these issues.\n\nThe effectiveness can vary depending on specific schools, regions, and individual experiences. Overall, it's a system with potential but requiring substantial improvements.",
